  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the effect of slowing heart rate upon both central
      and peripheral blood pressures using a medication called Ivabradine which slows heart rate
      without affecting heart contraction, and to compare the effects of ivabradine to a
      traditional blood pressure lowering medication called metoprolol (which is a beta-blocker).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
